  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nSetup: `resteasy-reactive`, `security`, proactive authentication is **disabled** (`quarkus.http.auth.proactive=false`)\r\n\r\nA `BlockingOperationNotAllowedException` is thrown when a resource method is annotated with `@RolesAllowed` and `@NonBlocking` and the method does not return an async type (`Uni<T>`).\r\n\r\nIt seems that permissions defined via config in `application.properties` work just fine.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe build should fail with a more informative error message.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nAn HTTP request fails at runtime.\r\n\r\n### How to Reproduce?\r\n\r\n1. Checkout https://github.com/mkouba/quarkus-quickstarts/tree/blocking-get-identity\r\n2. Run `mvn quarkus:dev` in the `security-jpa-quickstart`\r\n3. HTTP GET `http://localhost:8080/api/admin`\r\n\r\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Output of `java -version`\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Quarkus version or git rev\r\n\r\n999-SNAPSHOT\r\n\r\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\n\r\n_No response_",
